# import data
data <- read.csv("exam1.csv",head = T)
attach(data)
Distance..km. -> x
Error..m. -> y
plot(Distance..km.,Error..m.)

hist(Distance..km.)

# plotting the linear model will help us check assumption
plot(lm(y~x))

# do kernel regression
h = 9
x1 = seq(min(x),max(x),by=(max(x)-min(x))/99)
y1 = rep(0,100)
for(i in 1:100){
    y1[i] = sum(exp(-.5*((x1[i]-x)/h)^2)*y)/sum(exp(-.5*((x1[i]-x)/h)^2))
}

plot(x,y)
lines(x1,y1,col=2)
